      "author": "lavs9",
      "description": "## What's new\n\nFull Ghostty keybinding support — your `~/.config/ghostty/config` keybinds now work inside the embedded terminal.\n\n### Changes\n- **Copy/paste now work**: `cmd+c` copies selected text, `cmd+v` pastes from clipboard\n- **`shift+enter` inserts a newline** in Claude and other apps that use the kitty keyboard protocol (`\\x1b[13;2u`)\n- **All `keybind =` lines parsed** from your Ghostty config — custom bindings are respected and override defaults\n- Supports `copy_to_clipboard`, `paste_from_clipboard`, and `text:STRING` actions (with `\\e`/`\\n`/`\\r`/`\\t` escape sequences)\n- Built-in defaults always active even without a config file: `cmd+c`, `cmd+v`, `shift+enter`, `cmd+enter`\n\n### Files\n- `main.js` — bundled plugin\n- `manifest.json` — plugin manifest",
