      "author": "lavs9",
      "description": "## Fix: Zombie pty_helper.py processes\n\nWhen Obsidian quits or the plugin is unloaded, `pty_helper.py` processes were not killed and continued running at high CPU (99%+), draining battery.\n\n### Changes\n- Add `killPty()` method that closes all stdio pipes, sends SIGTERM, and falls back to SIGKILL\n- Implement `onunload()` to kill all PTY processes across terminal views\n- Add SIGTERM/SIGHUP signal handlers in `pty_helper.py`\n- Add watchdog thread that detects parent death and force-exits within ~2 seconds\n- Close inherited fds in child process to ensure pipes break cleanly",
